Purpose of Scope Boundaries

The scope boundaries define the limits of the Blood Bank Management System project by clearly specifying what is included and excluded. This helps prevent scope creep and ensures clarity among stakeholders.

In-Scope (Included)

The system will include the following:

Secure user authentication and role-based access

Donor registration and donor profile management

Blood inventory management by blood group and quantity

Tracking of blood stock expiration dates

Blood request and allocation management

Emergency blood request handling

Search functionality for blood availability

Basic reporting (donors, inventory, usage)

Notifications for low stock levels and donor reminders

Centralized and secure database management

Out-of-Scope (Excluded)

The system will not include the following:

Mobile application development (Android/iOS)

Online payment or billing systems

Integration with laboratory blood testing equipment

National-level blood bank or government databases

Blood transportation and logistics tracking

AI/ML-based prediction and advanced analytics

Ambulance or emergency service integration

Multi-language and voice-based interfaces

Assumptions

Users have basic internet access and web browser support

Authorized users will operate the system responsibly

Data entered into the system is accurate and verified by staff

Constraints

Limited project duration and academic timeline

Development resources restricted to student team

Web-based implementation using standard tools

Conclusion

This scope boundaries document clearly defines the functional limits of the Blood Bank Management System and ensures focused development aligned with project goals and constraints.
